==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Poop
<hw>Poop</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Pooped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pooping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. D. <ets>poepen</ets>. See
<er>Pop</er>.]</ety> <def>To make a noise; to pop; also, to break
wind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poop</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Poop
<hw>Poop</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>poupe</ets>; cf. Sp. & Pg.
<ets>popa</ets>, It. <ets>poppa</ets>; all fr. L.
<ets>puppis</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A deck raised above
the after part of a vessel; the hindmost or after part of a vessel's
hull; also, a cabin covered by such a deck. See <cref>Poop deck</cref>,
under <er>Deck</er>. See also <er>Roundhouse</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With wind in <qex>poop</qex>, the vessel plows the sea.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>poop</qex> was beaten gold.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poop</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Poop
<hw>Poop</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>To
break over the poop or stern, as a wave.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A sea which he
thought was going to <xex>poop</xex> her.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Lord Dufferin.</au>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>To strike in the stern, as by collision.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pooped</ent>⟦br⟧
